{
  "_comment": [
    "Patch contacts. Copy or edit this file to:",
    "  Flatpak:  ~/.var/app/land.rob.patch/config/patch/contacts.json",
    "  Source:   ~/.config/patch/contacts.json",
    "Patch will pick up changes on next start.",
    "",
    "Format: a flat JSON object. Pairs can run either way —",
    "  \"name\": \"number\"   (most natural — like a phonebook)",
    "  \"number\": \"name\"   (also accepted)",
    "Numbers are normalised to E.164 with US as the default country, so",
    "'713-555-1234' and '7135551234' both resolve to '+17135551234',",
    "which is the form cheogram uses on the wire.",
    "",
    "Folks (libfolks) is the long-term plan — when it lands in the GNOME",
    "Platform flatpak, the system address book overlays on top of this",
    "file. Until then, this is the source of truth for caller-ID names",
    "in the call dialog, conversation list, recents, voicemail, and",
    "group-message sender labels.",
    "",
    "Remove this _comment field in your own file — only string-to-string",
    "pairs are interpreted as contacts."
  ],

  "Alice Example": "713-555-1234",
  "Bob Example":   "+18325551234",
  "Carol":         "(346) 555-9876"
}
